    "Id": "Weapon_Flamer_Ryuujin",
    "Name": "Ryuujin Flamer",
    "Details": "Developed by Howa Machinery Company Ltd. for the King Dragon, the experimental Ryujin Superheavy Flamer utilizes a totally new concept for delivery of the flammable substance. The weapon charges a 'cloud' of inert nano-particles with an positive charge, which then binds a special ionized highly flammable substance between the particles. Upon impact with a surface the bindings of the nano-particles and the flammable substance are broken, resulting in the ignition of the fluid by the released electrical charge. This allows the flamer to reach much further distances, but also means the heat explosion is considerably less at shorter distances as the kinetic impact will rupture less of the bindings. If the weapon is handled incorrectly it could lead to an incorrect charging sequence resulting in the flammable substance igniting upon firing, causing a large heat explosion. <b><color=#F79232>Uses Superheavy Flamer Ammo.</color></b>",
